title: Reasoning about RVs that are 1 when Uniform RV is within bounds
---
body:

## Problem

Let $X \sim \text{Uniform}(0,1)$. 

Let $a, b$ be constants satisfying $0 < a < b < 1$.

Let $Y=1 (0 < X < b)$.

Let $Z=1 (a < X < 1)$.

(a) Are $X$ and $Y$ independent?

(b) Find $E(Y \vert Z)$.

